The Global Strategic Stability Utility (GSSU) - "The Immutable Dome"
Founding Principle: The system exists to defend any sovereign territory from unauthorized ballistic missile attack. It is a firebreak for civilization, not a tool for any alliance.

1. Universal Membership & Mandatory Inclusion
All UN-recognized states are automatically covered. Protection is a condition of the system's existence, not a subscription.

No opt-out for major powers. China, Russia, the US, India, UK, France, Pakistan, Israel, North Korea – all are under the Dome. Their missile sites are protected from third-party attacks, and their launches are subject to the same intercept logic.

2. Revolutionary Governance: The Ternary Council
Power is divided among three mutually distrusting blocs, each with a hard veto. No single bloc can weaponize the system.

Bloc A: NATO & US Allies (USA, UK, Japan, Australia, EU, etc.)

Bloc B: The Shanghai Cooperation Core (China, Russia, Central Asian states)

Bloc C: The Non-Aligned & Neutral Bloc (India, Brazil, Indonesia, Switzerland, UAE, etc. – a rotating leadership council)

The Rule of Engagement: A defensive intercept can only be authorized if TWO of the three Blocs' AI-Councils independently verify and agree that:

A ballistic missile launch has been detected.

The launch trajectory is predicted to impact a populated sovereign territory.

The launch was not pre-declared as a test to a shared transparency portal.

If only one Bloc calls for an intercept, nothing happens. This prevents any one power from hijacking the system for a first strike under false pretenses.

3. The Funding Model: Global Security Surcharge
Instead of "renting protection," the system is funded as a global public good, akin to funding the WHO or IAEA, but with a mandatory levy.

Formula: (0.15% of GDP) + (0.05% of Annual Military Budget)

Example:

USA (GDP $25T, MilBudget $800B): ~$37.5B + $0.4B = $37.9B/year

China (GDP $18T, MilBudget $300B): ~$27B + $0.15B = $27.15B/year

Luxembourg (GDP $85B, MilBudget $0.5B): ~$0.13B + negligible = $0.13B/year

Economic Incentive: This directly ties the cost to a nation's ability to pay and its contribution to global insecurity (via its military spending). It creates a financial incentive for disarmament.

4. The "Covenant of Transparency & Safety" (CTS)
All members must adhere to:

Article 1: Launch Transparency. All ballistic missile tests (including SLBMs) must be logged 72 hours in advance in the shared portal, with expected impact zones. Failure to do so risks an intercept.

Article 2: No First-Use Pledge. To be under the Dome, all nuclear states must formally and verifiably adopt a No-First-Use policy. The Dome is your guarantee.

Article 3: Inspection & Verification. Each Bloc has permanent, rotating inspection teams at the other Blocs' ground stations and command centers.

Article 4: The Sanctuary Rule. The Dome never engages:

Sub-orbital artillery or short-range rockets (<350km range).

Cruise missiles or hypersonic glide vehicles in atmospheric flight.

Any launch declared to a UN-sanctioned space agency for peaceful orbital insertion.

5. Technological Implementation: The Triplicated "Guardian AI"
The kill chain is managed not by one AI, but by three identical "Guardian" AIs, each physically hosted and maintained by one of the three Blocs.

Process: Satellite detects launch → Data stream is sent simultaneously to AI-A (Texas), AI-B (Shanghai), and AI-C (Bangalore).

Consensus: Each AI runs its threat assessment. They communicate via a cryptographically-secured, quantum-key-distributed channel.

Action: Only if AI-A and AI-C, or AI-B and AI-C agree, is the fire command sent. If A and B agree but C disagrees, the command is locked. This makes collusion between two blocs against the third nearly impossible, as the third's AI is an immutable part of the circuit.

6. Strategic Impact & Deterrence Shift
This doesn't eliminate nuclear weapons. It radically changes their utility.

Deterrence becomes purely second-strike. Your missiles are safe in their silos from a decapitation strike by a third party. You can ride out an attack and retaliate. This reinforces stability.

It eliminates "bolt-from-the-blue" attacks and regional nuclear blackmail. No one can launch a surprise ICBM attack expecting it to land. The only conceivable use of nukes becomes a desperate, second-strike response to an overwhelming conventional invasion—a much higher threshold.

It creates an unprecedented crisis communication mechanism. The Ternary Council becomes the most important room in the world during any missile crisis, forcing cooperation between adversaries.

